## Evaluation Integration Considerations

For structured evaluation of the simulation framework, the following technical alignment points are typically required:

- Defined technical point of contact for coordination and testing  
- Clearly scoped use case or system scenario for simulation  
- Access to a controlled or sandbox environment (e.g., Google Cloud)  
- Relevant system architecture context (dependency structure, topology, service mapping)  
- Agreed evaluation criteria for resilience and failure propagation analysis  
- High-level timeline for iterative testing and review  

These inputs ensure accurate mapping of system dependencies and consistent evaluation of the supervisory resilience model.
